cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on modeling contextualized sentence representations with visual awareness, which involves both natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses a pre-trained cross-modal embedding space, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture that involves attention mechanisms, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Furthermore, the paper applies the proposed method to three different tasks, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
